This paper deals with text classification and information retrieval, which are core topics in the field of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques such as bag-of-words representation and section weighting, which are commonly used in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the performance of different classification models, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with disease outbreak reports, which can be considered a topic in cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
